es (`active` тЖТ `idle` тЖТ `ended`), warnings, errors. Key fields: `component`, `hook`, `strategy`, `session_id`.\n- **git-log.txt**: Commit graph showing main branch, `entire/checkpoints/v1`, checkpoint initialization.\n- **git-tree.txt**: Files at HEAD vs checkpoint branch (separated by `--- entire/checkpoints/v1 ---`).\n- **checkpoint-metadata/**: `metadata.json` has `checkpoint_id`, `strategy`, `files_touched`, `token_usage`, and `sessions` array. Session subdirs have per-session details.\n\n### 6. Report findings\n\nIdentify whether the issue is in:\n- **CLI hooks** (prepare-commit-msg, commit-msg, post-commit)\n- **Session management** (phase transitions, session tracking)\n- **Checkpoint creation** (branch management, metadata writing)\n- **Attribution** (file tracking, prompt correlation)\n- **Strategy logic** (auto-commit vs manual-commit behavior)\n\n\nARGUMENTS: /Users/alex/workspace/cli/e2e/artifacts/2026-02-26T11-45-27 - this had failures (main branch)\n\nand it seems like subsquent runs are fine /Users/alex/workspace/cli/e2e/artifacts/2026-02-26T12-02-11\n\nnon-deterministic agent behaviour? or something else?\n\n---\n\nis the claude invocation in the e2e's picking up user settings? we shouldn't be, right?\n\n---\n\ncould we enable sandboxing? https://code.claude.com/docs/en/settings#sandbox-settings\n\n---\n\nthe 'auth' fixes we did yesterday to use keychain based auth - do we even need the claude dir to copy anything?\n\n---\n\nlet's try it\n\n---\n\nBase directory for this skill: /Users/alex/.claude/skills/tdd-dev\n\n# TDD Developer\n\nImplement features using Test-Driven Development and Clean Code principles.\n\n## TDD Cycle\n\n1. **Red** - Write failing test first\n2. **Green** - Minimal code to pass\n3. **Refactor** - Clean up, tests stay green\n\n## Clean Code Standards\n\n- **Names reveal intent** - Variables, functions, classes\n- **Small functions** - One responsibility each\n- **DRY** - Extract duplication\n- **SOLID** - Single responsibility, Open/closed, Liskov, Interface segregation, Dependency inversion\n- **Self-documenting** - Comments explain \"why\", not \"what\"\n\nAlways consider: edge cases, input validation, security, performance, concurrency.\n\n## Development Workflow\n\n### 1. Understand Requirements\n\nRead `docs/requirements/[feature]/README.md` for specifications.\n\n### 2. Check for Review Feedback\n\nLook for `review-NN.md` files in the requirements folder:\n\n```markdown\n# In review-NN.md, update status line:\n> Status: pending    тЖТ when review is new\n> Status: in-progress тЖТ when addressing\n> Status: addressed   тЖТ when complete\n```\n\nAddress each issue before proceeding.\n\n### 3. Plan Tasks\n\nBreak work into testable increments. Create task files in `docs/requirements/[feature]/`:\n\n```markdown\n# Task NN: [Short Description]\n\n> Status: todo\n\n## Goal\nWhat this accomplishes.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Criterion 1\n- [ ] Criterion 2\n\n## Notes\nImplementation notes, decisions, blockers.\n```\n\nUpdate status: `todo` тЖТ `in-progress` тЖТ `done`\n\n### 4. Implement (TDD)\n\nFor each task:\n\n1. Write failing test\n2. Run test (confirm red)\n3. Write minimal implementation\n4. Run test (confirm green)\n5. Refactor if needed\n6. Run full validation\n\n### 5. Validate After Each Step\n\nRun after every change:\n\n```bash\n# Linting/formatting (adjust to project)\nmise run list\n\n# Tests\nmise run test\n```\n\nFix failures immediately before proceeding.\n\n## Final Report\n\nWhen complete, summarize:\n\n- What was implemented\n- Tests added\n- Design decisions and trade-offs\n- Issues encountered\n- Suggested next steps\n\n\nARGUMENTS: Fix E2E test isolation: Claude Code invocations in E2E tests are picking up user settings (~/.claude/CLAUDE.md, projects/, plugins/, etc.) when running locally. The fix: always set CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR to an empty temp dir (both locally and on CI), and on CI only symlink .claude.json into it for API key auth. Delete the broad isolat